message: #9442 This may be hilarious, but for me it is a huge issue. I have the feeling that I attract guys and people in general, but they somehow feel intimidated by me which makes me instantly act as if they were inferior to me. I am then too proud to make any move that could hint I am interested. Arguably enough, I grew up in Eastern Europe where they teach you "moral values" and where they cultivate your hubris as something honourable. I wish guys were more daring with me, more challenging in conversations, but they seem only interested in jumping your bones rather than fucking my mind.
